12/07/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The government has decided to abolish entrance visa requirements for Turkish citizens, effective Monday (July 12th), the day Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan kicks off a visit. 
He will meet with President Boris Tadic and Prime Minister Mirko Cvetkovic. 
The programme also includes a visit to the Muslim-dominated town of Novi Pazar. 
Erdogan arrives in Belgrade from Bosnia and Herzegovina, where he attended Sunday's commemoration of the 15th anniversary of the Srebrenica massacre. 
(Tanjug, B92, Beta, Zaman - 12/07/10; AFP, Hurriyet - 11/07/10)
